Fix DRM node type detection and dev_path on FreeBSD.

Two bugs in drm 0.14.1 on FreeBSD, addressed in one patch:

1. `DrmNode::from_dev_id` derives the node type from `minor(st_rdev) >> 6`.
   That works on Linux because the st_rdev minor number is the DRM device
   number, but on FreeBSD the kernel assigns st_rdev minor numbers
   unrelated to the DRM device number:

       /dev/drm/0   (card0, primary)    minor=192, minor>>6=3 (invalid)
       /dev/drm/128 (renderD128, render) minor=64,  minor>>6=1 (wrong: Control)

   Use devname() to get the kernel device name and parse the DRM device
   number out of it instead.

2. `dev_path` on FreeBSD has an operator precedence bug:

       let id = old_id & id_mask + ty.minor_base();

   `+` binds tighter than `&`, so the expression evaluates as
   `old_id & (id_mask + ty.minor_base())`. When asking for the render
   node derived from card0 (old_id = 0), this gives 0, producing
   "/dev/dri/card0" back as the render node path instead of
   "/dev/dri/renderD128". niri then falls back to using the primary node
   for rendering, which the NVIDIA driver refuses, and spins in a retry
   loop until the compositor hangs.

   upstream fixed this silently when refactoring the code in PR #210
   (released as 0.14.2), but 0.14.2 was later yanked from crates.io as
   a breaking-change mistake, so niri has dropped back to 0.14.1, where
   the bug is still present. Parenthesise to force the correct order.

3. Also fix `has_render` which was hardcoded to `false` on FreeBSD. With
   node type detection actually working, it can use the same
   `node_path(...).is_ok()` check as Linux.

--- a/src/node/mod.rs
+++ b/src/node/mod.rs
@@ -48,6 +48,7 @@
         //   0 -  63 -> Primary
         //  64 - 127 -> Control
         // 128 - 255 -> Render
+        #[cfg(not(target_os = "freebsd"))]
         let ty = match minor(dev) >> 6 {
             0 => NodeType::Primary,
             1 => NodeType::Control,
@@ -55,6 +56,24 @@
             _ => return Err(CreateDrmNodeError::NotDrmNode),
         };

+        // On FreeBSD the st_rdev minor number does not correspond to the DRM
+        // device number. Use devname() to read the kernel's name for the
+        // device ("drm/0", "drm/128") and parse the trailing integer.
+        #[cfg(target_os = "freebsd")]
+        let ty = {
+            let dev_name = devname(dev).ok_or(CreateDrmNodeError::NotDrmNode)?;
+            let drm_num_str = dev_name.trim_start_matches(|c: char| !c.is_numeric());
+            let drm_num: u32 = drm_num_str
+                .parse()
+                .map_err(|_| CreateDrmNodeError::NotDrmNode)?;
+            match drm_num >> 6 {
+                0 => NodeType::Primary,
+                1 => NodeType::Control,
+                2 => NodeType::Render,
+                _ => return Err(CreateDrmNodeError::NotDrmNode),
+            }
+        };
+
         Ok(DrmNode { dev, ty })
     }

